      name: "ORIGIN IV — Lüèduó (Quzghun → Raven)",
      era: "Tian Shan to Chang'an, late 9th century",
      blurb: "Among the Uyghur horse-clans at the foot of the Tian Shan, a child named Quzghun is born with golden-amber eyes whose pupils are not quite round; his mother dies bearing him and the camp passes him from tent to tent. Apprenticed to the shamans for his exceptional grace, he is dismissed at nine by the eldest shaman Chong ana, who tells him he carries a door inside himself she will not teach him to open. By seventeen he is beautiful and uncategorizable, working through every available woman until kindled blood-feuds force the clan chief to demand his death. The Tang army arrives in time to take him as a hostage, and he rides east in a wagon, watching the horizon with want. At a roadside stop the boy dances in patterns the shamans had forbidden him to repeat, and is sent on to court. At the Dragon Throne the Emperor renames him Lüèduó — Raven — and he climbs from prisoner to fixture, sleeping his way through the wives, daughters, concubines, and widows of ministers, generals, and merchants, collecting their secrets as other men collect jade. The eunuch majordomo Wei summons him, lays out exactly what he has been doing, and recruits him as a state asset; under Wei's training he becomes a cipher-using, identity-shifting agent of the Ministry of Rites, telling himself he is the spider at the centre of the web.",
