      name: "Episode III: To the Kurgan",
      era: "Above Merv to the bone chapel, 900 AD",
      blurb: "At dawn the company finds the kurgan ringed with poles of flayed skin — the cult sacrificed one of their own — and at the summit a portal opening onto Abu-Rayhan's ransacked library back in Merv. They step through into carnage: servants slaughtered, the amulet stolen, and a dead steppe-woman with Rahzalahn's silver hair-comb in her throat. Abu-Rayhan, Hind, and the Hermetic scholar Isaac arrive; Isaac identifies the amulet's pre-Egyptian origins. A second portal opens to the catacombs beneath Merv, where the company pursues the kidnappers through traps. A werewolf bursts from a niche and savages Earmack; Bansi drives it onto a wall-spike, but Earmack dies in Giovanni's arms receiving last rites. The company fights upward into a chamber lined with tens of thousands of skulls, where Karishkir, Drekhlo, and Nizack are about to sacrifice Rahzalahn on a black altar beneath the gold amulet. Bansi cuts Rahzalahn's bonds; Eskil and Drekhlo trade hammering blows; Karishkir's mental call fails on Eskil because his soul is 'already promised to another'; Isaac unleashes a flood of holy light. Karishkir and Drekhlo escape through Nizack's failing portal — Drekhlo vowing to drink Eskil's blood from his skull — but Nizack is left behind, and Bansi and Lüèduó drive silver daggers through his heart, disintegrating him.",
